Overlord II;Overlord II;Overlord II;;videos\Overlord II (2009).mp4;OK;images\Overlord II (2009).webp;;Steam;Triumph Studios;Codemasters;23/06/2009;Overlord II, sequel to the critically acclaimed cult hit, sees the return of the chaotic Minions and their new Dark Master. Bigger, badder and more beautifully destructive, Overlord 2 has a Glorious Empire to smash, a massive Netherworld to revive, Minion mounts to mobilize, a trio of mistresses to woo, War Machines to crush opposition and lots of cute creatures to, err... murder (and a mini-map);Role-playing (RPG), Adventure, Strategy, Hack and slash/Beat 'em up;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/12810/2094/1c2b02e764a8cb0617a047307feb3e4567095537/1750484520/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447352194;steam_12810
Operation Flashpoint Dragon Rising;Operation Flashpoint: Dragon Rising;Operation Flashpoint Dragon Rising;;;OK;images\Operation Flashpoint Dragon Rising (2009).webp;;Steam;Codemasters Southam;Codemasters;06/10/2009;"Operation Flashpoint: Dragon Rising is a game about a fictitious conflict on one of the Sakhalin islands, a conflict that is in danger of erupting onto a global scale. The player takes the role of a US soldier, part of the allied force fighting against outnumbering Chinese forces vying for control of the island.

The game centers on a campaign narrative that gives the player a variety of roles in the allied forces ranging from a Marine Infantry, tank commander, Special Forces and helicopter captain. The game has an incredible realistic depiction of war with careful attention to the detail of the weapons, equipment and tactics of the armed forces. The action is varied from intense fire fights through to slower pace tactical decision making on how to best tackle the mission objectives.";Strategy, Puzzle, Shooter, Simulator, Tactical;no_section;steam_12830
